# System Architecture Diagrams (IEEE Column Optimized)

This diagram is designed to be highly vertical and compact, making it perfect for fitting inside a single column of an IEEE paper.

```mermaid
graph TD
    %% Define Styles
    classDef hardware fill:#2d3436,stroke:#b2bec3,stroke-width:1px,color:#fff;
    classDef software fill:#0984e3,stroke:#74b9ff,stroke-width:1px,color:#fff;
    classDef algo fill:#6c5ce7,stroke:#a29bfe,stroke-width:1px,color:#fff;
    classDef act fill:#00b894,stroke:#55efc4,stroke-width:1px,color:#fff;

    %% Hardware / Input
    Cam["Webcam Capture<br>(1280x720)"]:::hardware
    Down["Downscale (640x360)"]:::software
    
    %% Split Path
    Cam --> Down
    Down -->|Spacebar<br>Calibration| Loc["Screen Localization<br>(SuperGlue/ORB)"]:::algo
    Down -->|Continuous| Track["MediaPipe<br>Hand Tracking"]:::software
    
    %% Localization Path
    Loc --> Hom["Homography &<br>Bounding Box"]:::software
    
    %% Sync point
    Hom -.->|Calibrated Bounds| Map["Coordinate Mapper"]:::software
    Track --> Map
    
    %% Output
    Map --> Engine["Gesture Engine"]:::software
    
    Engine -->|1 Finger| Move["Cursor Move"]:::act
    Engine -->|Pinch| Click["Left/Right Click"]:::act
    Engine -->|2 Fingers| Zoom["Scroll/Zoom"]:::act
    Engine -->|3/4 Fingers| Swipe["Desktop Swipe"]:::act
    Engine -->|5 Fingers| Pause["Freeze System"]:::act
```
